title.narrative: OUTPUT 5.2: SOCIAL PROTECTION

description.narrative: National and sub-national government partners have strengthened institutional capacities to develop and deliver child-sensitive social protection, particularly to children and families in the most-vulnerable situations, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Access To Inclusive Social Protection (Covid), Evaluation, Reducing Child Poverty, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, more disadvantaged and excluded children are benefiting from an improved policy environment and strengthened social protection system

description.narrative: After;the establishment of a transitional government, increasing social protection coverage was prioritized by the government of Sudan, to support children and families who are facing increasing poverty and vulnerability in the face of multiple crises including economic crisis, the COVID-19 pandemic and other shocks The capacities of both national and state ministries were strengthened with the roll-out of a new Maternal and Child Cash Transfers;programme;which aims to support pregnant women and children in the first 1,000 days with cash assistance as well as strengthened essential services.; | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:18/01/2022
